#
# Tokenizer differential-oracle goldens (ADR-0005). Each case pins one input's
# whole token stream: per token its byte span, TokenKind, and the exact source
# slice, with skipped whitespace/comment gaps shown as `trivia` lines so the
# interleaving reconstructs the source. The dialect rides in the directive
# (`tokens-ansi` / `tokens-postgres` / `tokens-mysql` / `tokens-mssql`). The SQL
# strings are hand-authored adversarial fixtures for the high-risk cursor cases
# the ADR calls out; the expected blocks are generated and the oracle invariants
# (UTF-8 boundaries, non-overlap, trivia-only gaps, reconstruction, kind/slice
# agreement) are checked on every regeneration. Rewrite with:
#   REWRITE=1 cargo test -p squonk-conformance goldens::tests::datadriven_golden_corpus --lib

# --- Multibyte UTF-8 (the headline char-boundary risk) ---

tokens-ansi
café = δ
----
source "café = δ"
0..5 Word "café"
5..6 trivia " "
6..7 Operator(Eq) "="
7..8 trivia " "
8..10 Word "δ"

