tokens-mssql
N'x'
----
source "N'x'"
0..4 String "N'x'"

# PostgreSQL has no `N'…'` national-string constant (its scanner reads `N'x'` as the
# identifier `nchar` + a separate string), so the PG preset leaves `national_strings`
# off and `N` lexes as a bare word (pg-national-strings-lexing-divergence).
tokens-postgres
N'x'
----
source "N'x'"
0..1 Word "N"
1..4 String "'x'"

